Built an integrated 3-statement financial model and a dynamic DCF valuation for Apple Inc with scenario and sensitivity analysis. DCF includes both perpetuity method and exit multiple method. Exit multiple is based on a trading comps analysis. The project covers 3 years of historical 10-K data (Income Statement, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow) with revenue projections across Apple's four business segments through FY2026–2031.
Key highlights:
→ Fully linked 3-statement model with a dedicated Assumptions sheet
→ DCF model using CAPM-based WACC and Gordon Growth Model terminal value
→ Sensitivity analysis varying WACC and terminal growth rate
→ Executive Summary with football field valuation chart and bull/bear case
